The paper proposes an algorithm for submodular maximization under knapsack constraints, which is a problem in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithm is also designed to be adversarially robust, which suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper mentions scalable implementations in distributed and streaming settings, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) or systems and networking (cs.SI).
